# ZenK UI - Project Rules

## CRITICAL: Reference this file before making any UI/component changes

## Tech Stack

- React (Vite)
- TailwindCSS
- Inter Font
- Heroicons (outline) - USE ONLY OUTLINE VARIANTS
- React Router
- react-chartjs-2 + Chart.js
- Axios

## UI Rules (MUST FOLLOW EXACTLY)

### Global Style

- Use Inter font everywhere - it's already configured in index.css
- Base background: #F8FAFC (Tailwind slate-50) - use `bg-slate-50`
- All cards MUST use: `rounded-xl bg-white shadow-sm border border-gray-200`
- Never deviate from these card styles

### Buttons

- Primary buttons: `bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white`
- Export buttons: ghost style with icon - use `text-gray-700 hover:bg-gray-50` with icon from Heroicons
- All buttons should have proper padding and rounded corners

### Icon Library

- ALWAYS use Heroicons Outline variants: `@heroicons/react/24/outline`
- Never use solid or mini variants
- Import pattern: `import { IconName } from '@heroicons/react/24/outline'`

### Sidebar

- Width: `w-64` (exactly)
- Left aligned
- Text-gray-700 for labels
- Icons + text layout: `flex gap-3 items-center`
- Active state: `bg-blue-50 text-blue-600`
- Hover state: `hover:bg-gray-50`

### Dashboard Layout Order (MUST FOLLOW)

When creating or modifying the dashboard, maintain this exact section order:

1. Top Filters Row
2. KPI Cards (4 columns grid)
   - Today's Sales
   - Today's Litres Sold
   - Cash in Hand
   - Profit Today
3. Charts Section
   - Line chart for daily sales
   - Bar chart for monthly litres
   - Donut chart for payment mode split
4. Fuel Tank Status
   - Petrol, Diesel, Power
   - Percentage bars with low fuel warning (<20%)
5. Alerts Panel
   - Red/Yellow alerts with proper styling
6. Latest Activity Table
   - Table format with export button
7. Quick Actions Panel
   - Add Sale, Add Expense, Add Credit, Update Price, Start/Close Shift

### Charts Config (MUST FOLLOW)

Use react-chartjs-2 + Chart.js

- Line chart: curved lines, tension=0.4 (already configured in chartConfig.js)
- Bar chart: soft rounded bars, borderRadius: 8
- Donut chart: centered labels, cutout: '60%'
- Always use the chart options from `src/utils/chartConfig.js`
- Maintain responsive design with `maintainAspectRatio: false` and container height

### Component Structure

- All components should be in appropriate folders:
  - Layout components: `src/components/`
  - Dashboard components: `src/components/dashboard/`
  - Pages: `src/pages/`
  - Utils: `src/utils/`

### Code Style

- Use functional components with hooks
- Follow React best practices
- Use TailwindCSS utility classes (no custom CSS unless absolutely necessary)
- Keep components modular and reusable
- Use proper TypeScript-like prop validation (consider PropTypes if needed)

### Color Palette

- Primary: blue-600/blue-700
- Success: green-600/green-50
- Warning: yellow-600/yellow-50
- Error: red-600/red-50
- Text: gray-700 (labels), gray-900 (headings), gray-500 (subtle text)
- Background: slate-50 (base), white (cards)

### Spacing & Layout

- Use Tailwind spacing scale (gap-3, gap-4, gap-6, p-4, p-6, etc.)
- Grid layouts: `grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4` for responsive design
- Consistent padding: p-6 for cards, p-4 for smaller elements

## IMPORTANT REMINDERS

- Before creating any new component, check if similar component exists
- Always use the card style: `rounded-xl bg-white shadow-sm border border-gray-200`
- Always use Heroicons Outline variants
- Always maintain the dashboard section order
- Always use Inter font (already configured globally)
- Always follow the color palette specified above
- Always use the chart configurations from chartConfig.js

## File Naming Conventions

- Components: PascalCase (e.g., `KPICards.jsx`)
- Files: match component name
- Folders: lowercase with dashes if needed (e.g., `dashboard/`)

